channel.description:
Hello,
Welcome to our project. The project is called "unnamed" at the moment due to the fact we could not think of a name yet...
The project consists of four people:
[ul][li]Fred[/li] [li]Byte me[/li] [li]Aelin[/li] [li]laz[/li][/ul]
The team is putting together all shorts of utilities to keep the project as much updated to RS as possible...
Programs we have made at this time beening: An updater *If you do not understand what it is then an example is below here* [code]Runescape updater
RS version: 544 Loaded 298 classes from raw/runescape.jar. Loaded 13 classes from raw/loader.jar.
Replacing classes: - Relpaced class fg - Relpaced class ng - Relpaced class ce - Relpaced class gj - Relpaced class ii Replaced 5/5 classes
ClientScript method: static final void cl.a(ui arg0, int arg1, int arg2)

[ Player ] ^ jj implements Player
[ More information ] - Failed to hook Character.getLoopCycleStatus!! - Failed to hook Client.getLoopCycle!! - MouseListener is class: ek.
Completed 4 transformer(s) in 584 ms.
[ Deobbing #544 Client ] - Class48 update masks. - Class42 OpCodes.
####################### # Defined 4/4 classes. # Defined Deobbed 2/2 classes. # Hooked 22/24 fields. # Created 0/1 "special methods." ####################### Packed 298 classes to hooked/runescape.jar.[/code] A packet Bot A world dumper I am working with KBot to get the client to dump all world objects and send it to my webserver. If you don't know what I mean; dumping all world objects while people are autoing. Stream renamer
Progress: Started to write up a basic network for the server... Wrote an update server and world loader...
